hone and listen when fetokakiss parents opened a restaurant in the mids he said pappas — a stranger — met with them and agreed to give them some equipment you ask yourself would you give help to someone you dont know said fetokakis his parents later repaid pappas pete comes from a time when character counted said nephew chris j pappas who runs pappas restaurants with his brother harris he could read a mans character and know that he was going to put his best efforts in houston was boomtown pappas was born in dallas in  and moved to houston in  with his three brothers their father a greek immigrant who owned restaurants in texas arkansas and tennessee had alerted them to a business opportunity in houston distributing refrigeration equipment houston was an upandcoming market said chris pappas they saw it as a boomtown in the s it was a very open town an accepting town to people moving here a wildcat town the brothers founded pappas refrigeration pete pappas patented several pieces of equipment including a commercial ice machine still used in the seafood industry according to chris pappas the brothers entrepreneurship led to their success according to a family friend he said the brothers figured out the secret to selling refrigeration equipment follow the ice truck around in  pappas and his brother jim left the equipment business and opened dot coffee shop followed shortly by the brisket house now pappas barbq jim pappas sons chris harris and gregory j pappas now deceased later joined the business the family went on to open the strawberry patch later reconceived as pappas bros steakhouse pappas seafood pappasitos pappadeaux and yia yia marys served in army air corps pappas stepped down as head of the family company several years ago but remained active he was essential to the siting of new restaurants said chris pappas until just a few weeks ago he continued to come to the pappas restaurants office on yale street pappas served in the army air corps during world war ii he served  with the inspector generals corps said his nephew he would inspect crash accidents the job did not deter the recreational pilot who enjoyed flying small planes to remote hunting areas pappas is remembered by some members of the restaurant community as a quiet but funloving leader alex brennanmartin whose family owns brennans of houston and commanders palace in new orleans described pappas contributions to the local restaurant scene as incalculable people say to me oh youre part of the brennan family and i chuckle he said what weve done is minuscule compared to the pappas family i admire them like i admire almost no one else pappas is survived by helen lucas pappas his wife of  years daughters pamela mattingly and mersina stubbs and five grandchildren services will be held at  am today at the annunciation greek orthodox cathedral  yoakum blvd in lieu of flowers the family requests memorials be directed to the star of hope and the ronald mcdonald house nickibrittonchroncom latest from the chroncom homepage click below for the top news from around the houston area and beyond sign up for our newsletters to be the first to learn about breaking news and more go to sign in and manage profile at the top of the page happening now severe thunderstorm warning rain in the forcast texas float fest off to a hot start saturday as trade deadline nears astros bullpen more vulnerable than drake parties at his popup houston strip club trending ‘justice league’ trailer offers first look at villain houston man must pay child support for kid thats not his celeb learns not to bring a loaded gun to the airport barbie collectors search for elusive treasures at local agreement reached on sweeping russia sanctions bill home alone actor found dead in calif hotel mexican resorts accused of drugging guests eva longoria shows off her bikini bod in ibiza woodlands pastor charged with prostitution khloe kardashian trolled hard after ojs parole celebrities reveal sneak peeks secrets at co