an staff image  of  mary pappas is photographed at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  mary pappas is photographed at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  photo mayra beltran staff image  of  mary pappas is photographed at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  mary pappas is photographed at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  photo mayra beltran staff image  of  the pappas barbecue restaurant house special includes pork ribs beef brisket ham pork sausage spicy rice and cucumber salad the pappas barbecue restaurant house special includes pork ribs beef brisket ham pork sausage spicy rice and cucumber salad photo mayra beltran staff image  of  beef brisket sandwhich at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  beef brisket sandwhich at pappas barbecue restaurant on friday oct   in houston  mayra beltran  houston chronicle  photo mayra beltran staff image  of  chris jc reid barbecue columnist chris jc reid barbecue columnist photo melissa phillip staff a new generation takes the reins at pappas restaurants    back to gallery there are few more recognizable names in houston than the pappas family weve all eaten at one of their restaurants pappas barbq for smoked meats pappadeaux for seafood and pappasitos for texmex just to name a few the pappas empire has grown from two restaurants in downtown houston in  to more than  restaurants in eight states today few houstonians know the story behind the family that has expanded pappas restaurants into one of the countrys largest familyowned restaurant chains it starts in  when hd pappas immigrated to america from greece he settled in dallas and raised four sons  jim pete tom and george the sons moved to houston in the s to start a successful refrigeration business  a growth industry at the time to say the least in addition to refrigeration equipment the brothers started selling other equipment to local restaurants they slowly started to get into the restaurant business themselves by the s they were concentrating on two of their restaurants in downtown houston both on pierce street the dot coffee shop where the metro station is now and the brisket house where a pappas barbq still is translator to read this article in one of houstons mostspoken languages click on the button below restaurants  bars the best deals of the  houston restaurant weeks zero degrees is expected to infuse houstons chinatown with  best bets for  houston restaurant weeks houston restaurant violations july  ihop offering cent pancakes tuesday around that time jims sons returned to houston  harris from the army and chris from college though the family business was successful the two wanted to strike out on their own harris took a job at the lubys cafeteria chain chris sold bibles doortodoor and later took a job at a dennys restaurant it was during this time that harris and chris learned every aspect of the restaurant business from dish washing to cooking to serving and management in  they took over daytoday management of the family restaurants and laid the foundation for the business it is today greg pappas another brother involved in the family business died in a car accident in  harris and chris still are directly involved in daytoday operation of pappas restaurants but over the past few years their children have taken on more prominent roles they live in a world where nothing is ever good enough nothing is ever completed says christina pappas referring to standards set by her father harris and uncle chris like a lot of heirs to texas food empires the sense of responsibility and pressure to continue the success of the family business is palpable but the new generation of pappas family restaurateurs seems to take it in stride six pappas children all in their s and s are involved in daytoday operations christina handles marketing and guest relations while her sister mary handles restaurant operations another sister evy is an architect and oversees restaurant construction brother hd manages real estate interests and younger brother tom just joined the business and is working at their newest concept pappas meat co chris daughter georgea heads up culinary research and development mary literally grew up in the family business  at the time her dad and uncle took over the downtown restaurants they were living in the  main apartment tower across the street my dad told all the employees he lived there so he could watch them all the time mary said after college mary started as a manager at a pappadeaux location not long after that pappas acquired the luthers barbq chain and mary oversaw its merger with pappas although her background is in barbecue mary now oversees business operations for all pappas restaurants mary is quick to point out that pappas still is a familyowned business investors and shareholders arent a factor in decision making thats critical in the cyclical nature of the restaurant business whereas some chains will lay off employees and switch to lower quality ingredients to keep profits up during tough times pappas has the resources and the independence to ride out the slumps many employees work for pappas their whole lives and two of the original employees hired by chris and harris pappas still are involved with the company though there is a fasttrack program for college graduates to become managers almost all of their restaurant managers started as servers or cooks and all managers are promoted from within the company it all makes for consistency in management in a large restaurant chain the new generation of the pappas family is fully aware of the vagaries of the restaurant business and the brutal competition they are sure to encounter in the future we like competition christina said it keeps us on our toes jc reid columnist houston chronicle business texas oil fields fuel meth boom houston living with glioblastoma houston nurse vows to make the most of john mcclain texans bill obrien ready to move beyond another  season movies  tv ghost story haunts viewer as meditation on passing of time top about our company ad choices careers terms of use advertising privacy policy your privacy rights your california privacy rights contact subscribe enewspaper archives customer service frequently asked questions newsroom contacts connect newsletters facebook twitter linkedin pinterest google connect   hearst newspapers llc pappas restaurants  wikipedia pappas restaurants from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search this article has multiple issues please help improve it or discuss these issues on the talk page learn how and when to remove these template messages this article needs additional citations for verification please help improve this article by adding citations to reliable sources unsourced material may be challenged and removed january  learn how and when to remove this template message this article includes a list of references but its sources remain unclear because it has insufficient inline citations please help to improve this article by introducing more precise citations january  learn how and when to remove this template message this article contains content that is written like an advertisement please help improve it by removing promotional content and inappropriate external links and by adding encyclopedic content written from a neutral point of view february  learn how and when to remove this template message learn how and when to remove this template message a pappadeaux seafood restaurant in dallas texas pappas restaurants is a privately owned restaurant group with its headquarters in houston texas the founders are greekamerican brothers pete and jim pappas the first restaurant was a greek grill in louisiana it opened in  in  its name was changed to pappas barbq since then the pappas family has opened  unique restaurants with more than  locations in texas colorado arizona illinois ohio new mexico georgia and alabama in the december  issue of texas monthly pappas bros steakhouse was named the best steakhouse in texas since  pappas bros steakhouse houston has been the recipient of the wine spectator grand award pappas bros steakhouse dallas has held the same award since  contents  history  restaurant brands  see also  references  external links historyedit pappas barbq  pierce street downtown houston the familyowned pappas restaurants inc chain operates in more than  locations in houston birmingham dallas cincinnati austin san antonio beaumont atlanta chicago denver albuquerque and phoenix the restaurants encompass a variety of concepts including pappas bros steakhouse pappadeaux seafood kitchen pappas seafood house pappasitos cantina pappas barbq pappas burger and yia yia marys the company is run by brothers christopher and harris pappas who also serve as the executive team at lubys inc a cafeteria chain in several states the origins of the familyoperated pappas restaurants dates back several generations beginning with hd pappas who emigrated from greece in  and opened restaurants in arkansas tennessee and texas in  hd pappass sons pete and jim moved to houston where they obtained a franchise to sell beer coolers in south texas the brothers eventually built the venture into a successful restaurant supply business selling chairs booths refrigerators and other kitchen equipment the business was cyclical however and the brothers soon decided to try the restaurant field in  with the opening of dot coffee shop off of i south just inside the  loop of houston in  jim pappass son harris joined the family business soon followed by his other sons christopher and greg the dot coffee shop in houston opened in  was the first restaurant venture by the second generation of the pappas family after jim pappass death in  his sons aggressively expanded the business opening more seafood restaurants as well as profitable mexican and cajun restaurants the pappas brothers grew the business on a tireless attention to detail value and service they also made their mark by offering large portions at moderate prices at restaurants with highly visible locations what the restaurants tended to lose in higher food costs they made up for with volume and considerable customer turnover the company had a competitive edge on publicly owned restaurant chains which were under pressure to build new units in a hurry and to improve their bottom lines from one quarter to the next unlike these competitors the pappas business could take its time in building a high quality restaurant devoting as much labor to the project as was required in  after concentrating their business in houston with more than  pappas dining spots the family began expanding into dallas and austin in  the business broke into the san antonio market with one of its pappasitos cantina mexican food eateries the company planned to open another pappasitos and the pappas cajun seafood concept pappadeux seafood kitchen in san antonio by the fall of  each of these restaurants included  to  square feet  m of space was designed by the pappas architectural staff and was built by the companys inhouse construction crew the company was shaken when greg pappas died in a car accident on a houston highway with his death in february  the company lost an important member of its executive team as well as its main architect in  the companys gamble on a new concept  an upscale steakhouse with a cigar room impressive wine cellar and playful art raised the business to new heights the company opened its first pappas bros steakhouse on the spot of the strawberry patch american bistro an eatery they had opened in  and closed in  the steakhouse represented a departure from the companys other causal dining restaurants and poised it for future growth another pappas steakhouse was opened in  located in the restaurant row that had developed along northwest highway in dallas the company took more than a year to build this restaurant with a wine list of  selections a cigar room and other amenities the restaurant proved a success in catering to business executives and those with a taste for fine food at the same time the company continued to expand its family empire with the opening of new restaurants in chicago and atlanta restaurant brandsedit pappadeaux seafood kitchen  pappasito’s cantina  pappas seafood house  pappas bros steakhouse  pappas barbq  yia yia mary’s  pappas burger  pappas grill  steakhouse  dot coffee shop see alsoedit houston portal companies portal food portal list of barbecue restaurants list of seafood restaurants referencesedit  main office pappas restaurants retrieved on january    northwest freeway houston tx   pappas bros steakhouse houston wine spectator  retrieved    pappas bros steakhouse dallas wine spectator  retrieved    httpclassaggienetworkcomclasspappashtml external linksedit pappas restaurants retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlepappasrestaurantsoldid categories companies based in houstonrestaurants in houstonbarbecue restaurantsrestaurants established in europeanamerican culture in houstongreekamerican culture in texas establishments in texasseafood restaurants in the united stateshidden categories articles needing additional references from january all articles needing additional referencesarticles lacking intext citations from january all articles lacking intext citationsarticles with a promotional tone from february all articles with a promotional tone navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what link